English
***Instructions for use***
To enter work schedules or news, the employee's data will be requested:
First the name of the employee will be requested, there you must enter only the first name without last name. Then the citizenship card will be requested, if the name and card number match the data of an employee in the mine database, access is allowed.
If the name does not match the identification number registered in the mine database, access will not be allowed and the employee will be informed that it does not exist in the mine database and will be invited to register the details of the new employee in the mine database. or to verify the data. To save the new employee you must do it in the code. You can replace the data of a registered employee, otherwise you will have to expand the array where the database is being simulated and add the new employee to the next position.
There are currently 3 employees in the mine database with the following information.

Employee 1:
Name: Carlos
Last name: Perez
gender: Male
ID: 101010
Hours worked: 1920

Employee 2:
Name: Sara
Last name: Ossa
gender: Fem
ID: 101020
Hours worked: 2000

Employee 3:
Name: Santiago
Last name: Smith
gender: Male
ID: 101030
Hours worked: 2120

When entering work days, it is not allowed to enter dates more than 1 day apart, the entry and exit time must be in the 24-hour format, and must be entered in the following format HH:mm
The arrival and departure dates must be entered in the dd/MM/YYYY format or can also be entered in the dd-MM-YYYY format (Both the date and time must not contain spaces).

To extend a license you must access it as if you were going to request it. At a certain point, a menu will appear asking you if you want to request a license or extend it.

Note: Only licenses that have been partially taken can be extended. If you have taken all the maximum days allowed for the license, you cannot extend it or request it again.

